Usage:
./verifyCert <pathToYourCert>

e.g. ./verifyCert ../myOwnCA/certs/server.crt

By default, all trusted CA certs are already installed under /etc/ssl/certs.


Reference: 

1.http://fm4dd.com/openssl/certverify.htm

2. https://zakird.com/2013/10/13/certificate-parsing-with-openssl

3. http://stackoverflow.com/questions/25482199/verify-a-certificate-chain-using-openssl-verify
